# Job Control Demonstration with `mysplit`

This example demonstrates how to use job control commands (e.g., `fg`, `bg`, `ctrl-z`, `ctrl-c`) in a Unix/Linux shell. It involves running multiple instances of the `./mysplit` program and managing them using shell job control.

## Commands and Actions

### 1. Start Multiple Processes

> ./mysplit 100 &
>./mysplit 101 &
./mysplit 102 &
./mysplit 103
